			<h2>Researchers Show How Brain’s Wiring Leads to Cognitive Control</h2>
					<p class="deck">Researchers convert brain scans into “wiring diagrams” of connections between brain regions to show which parts exert most “cognitive control” over thoughts and actions</p>
		<p class="byline">By <a href="http://ucrtoday.ucr.edu/author/snealon" title="View all posts by Sean Nealon" rel="author">Sean Nealon</a> on <em>October 1, 2015</em></p>			<div class="share">
			<p>Share this article: </p>
			<ul class="share_links">
